.Dd July 2025
.Dt MORIARTY\-BASH\-RULES 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm moriarty\-bash\-rules
.Nd bash command validation rules and pattern fragments for moriarty
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Bash rules provide command\-level validation specifically for Bash tool calls
in Claude Code.
They are configured as
.Ic [[bash_rules]]
entries in
.Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml
and are evaluated only when no tool rule
.Pq see Xr moriarty\-tool\-rules 5
has matched the Bash tool call.
.Pp
Rules are evaluated top\-to\-bottom with
.Em first\-match\-wins
semantics.
Place more specific rules before general ones.
.Sh CONFIGURATION
.Ss File Location
.Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml
.Pp
The path respects
.Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
if set.
.Ss Rule Structure
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "descriptive\-name"
pattern = "regex\-pattern"
action = { type = "ActionType", ... }
.Ed
.Ss Fields
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic name
A descriptive name for the rule, used in log output.
.It Ic pattern
A regular expression
.Pq Rust regex syntax
to match against the bash command.
Pattern fragments may be used with
.Ql {{fragment_name}}
syntax; see
.Sx PATTERN FRAGMENTS .
.It Ic action
The action to take when the pattern matches.
See
.Sx ACTIONS .
.El
.Sh ACTIONS
.Ss Allow
Explicitly allow the command to execute without user confirmation.
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "allow\-git\-status"
pattern = "^git\e\es+status"
action = { type = "Allow" }
.Ed
.Ss Deny
Block the command and show an error message to the user.
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "deny\-rm\-rf"
pattern = "^rm\e\es+\-rf\e\es+/"
action = { type = "Deny", value = "Recursive delete of root is not allowed" }
.Ed
.Ss Modify
Transform the command before execution using regex capture groups
.Pq $0, $1, $2, etc. .
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "add\-dry\-run"
pattern = "^(docker\e\es+system\e\es+prune)"
action = { type = "Modify", value = "$1 \-\-dry\-run" }
.Ed
.Pp
.Sy Security Warning :
Modify actions use unescaped capture group replacement.
Avoid patterns like
.Ql ^docker (.*)
that capture arbitrary input.
Use specific patterns like
.Ql ^(docker\e\es+system\e\es+prune)$
instead.
.Ss Ask
Defer to the user for case\-by\-case authorization.
Claude Code will prompt the user to approve or deny.
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "ask\-for\-sudo"
pattern = "^sudo\e\eb"
action = { type = "Ask" }
.Ed
.Ss ArgumentFilter
Structurally remove, add, or replace command arguments before execution.
Unlike
.Cm Modify ,
.Cm ArgumentFilter
manipulates arguments as discrete tokens,
making it easier to handle flags regardless of their position.
.Pp
.Sy Important :
After filtering, the modified command is automatically re\-validated
against all rules.
The filtered command must match an
.Cm Allow
rule (or be manually approved via
.Cm Ask )
to execute.
Chained ArgumentFilter rules are prevented to avoid infinite loops.
.Pp
.Em Removing arguments :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "cargo\-doc\-no\-browser"
pattern = "^cargo doc.*\-\-open"
action = { type = "ArgumentFilter", remove = ["\-\-open", "\-o"],
           reason = "Browser flags removed" }
.Ed
.Pp
The
.Ic remove
field supports exact matches
.Pq Ql \-\-open
and prefix matches
.Pq Ql \-\-open No also removes Ql \-\-open=browser .
Arguments are removed regardless of position.
.Pp
.Em Adding arguments :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "docker\-run\-safety"
pattern = "^docker run(?!.* \-\-read\-only)"
action = { type = "ArgumentFilter",
           add = ["\-\-read\-only", "\-\-security\-opt=no\-new\-privileges"],
           reason = "Added security restrictions" }
.Ed
.Pp
Arguments are appended to the end of the command.
.Pp
.Em Replacing arguments
.Pq combining remove and add :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "rm\-force\-interactive"
pattern = "^rm .*\-f"
action = { type = "ArgumentFilter",
           remove = ["\-f", "\-\-force"],
           add = ["\-i"],
           reason = "Replaced force with interactive" }
.Ed
.Pp
.Em Operation order :
.Bl -enum -offset indent -compact
.It
Remove specified arguments.
.It
Replace specified arguments (if the
.Ic replace
field is used).
.It
Add new arguments.
.El
.Sh PATTERN FRAGMENTS
Pattern fragments allow defining reusable regex snippets referenced in
rule patterns using
.Ql {{fragment_name}}
syntax.
.Ss Defining Fragments
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[pattern_fragments]
safe_chars = "[^|&;$\`()<>{}]"

[[bash_rules]]
name = "allow\-ls"
pattern = "^ls{{safe_chars}}*$"
action = { type = "Allow" }
.Ed
.Ss Nested Fragments
Fragments can reference other fragments.
Expansion happens in multiple passes:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[pattern_fragments]
safe_chars = "[^|&;$\`()<>{}]"
safe_arg = "( {{safe_chars}}+)"
safe_pipe = "( \e\e| (head|tail|grep){{safe_arg}}*)"
.Ed
.Ss Built\-in Default Fragments
.Nm moriarty
provides the following default fragments:
.Bl -tag -width "safe_pipe_cmd" -compact
.It Ic safe_chars
.Ql [^|&;$\`()<>{}]
\(em characters that don't allow shell injection.
.It Ic identifier
.Ql [a\-zA\-Z_][a\-zA\-Z0\-9_\-]*
\(em valid identifier pattern.
.It Ic number
.Ql [0\-9]+
\(em numeric values.
.It Ic safe_arg
.Ql "( [^|&;$\`()<>{}]+)"
\(em safe command argument.
.It Ic safe_flag
.Ql "( \-[a\-zA\-Z_][a\-zA\-Z0\-9_\-]*)"
\(em safe command flag.
.It Ic safe_path
Safe file path (no shell metacharacters).
.It Ic safe_pipe_cmd
.Ql (head|tail|grep|wc|sort|uniq)
\(em safe pipe target commands.
.It Ic safe_pipe
Safe command piping using
.Ic safe_pipe_cmd .
.El
.Pp
User\-defined fragments with the same name override the defaults.
.Ss Fragment Naming Rules
Fragment names must start with a letter or underscore
.Pq Ql [a\-zA\-Z_]
and may contain letters, numbers, underscores, and hyphens
.Pq Ql [a\-zA\-Z0\-9_\-]* .
.Ss Circular Dependencies
Fragments cannot reference each other in a cycle.
The system detects circular dependencies and reports an error
when loading the configuration.
.Sh SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
.Bl -enum
.It
.Em Block shell injection characters.
Exclude
.Ql | , & , ; , $ , \` , ( , ) , < , > , { , }
unless explicitly needed:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
pattern = "^ls( [^|&;$\`()<>{}]+)?$"
.Ed
.It
.Em Use anchors.
Always anchor with
.Ql ^
and
.Ql $
to prevent partial matching.
Without anchors,
.Ql git status
would also match
.Ql git status && rm \-rf / .
.It
.Em Escape regex metacharacters.
Remember to escape
.Ql \e\e , ( , ) , [ , ] , { , } , \&. , * , + , ? , |
in patterns.
.It
.Em Order rules from specific to general.
Deny rules for dangerous commands should come before
broader allow rules.
.It
.Em Use fragments for security patterns.
Define injection\-safe character classes once and reuse them.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Ss Safe Cargo Commands
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[pattern_fragments]
safe_chars = "[^|&;$\`()<>{}]"

[[bash_rules]]
name = "cargo\-doc\-no\-browser"
pattern = "^cargo doc.*\-\-open"
action = { type = "ArgumentFilter", remove = ["\-\-open", "\-o"],
           reason = "Browser not useful for Claude" }

[[bash_rules]]
name = "cargo\-safe\-commands"
pattern = "^cargo (build|check|test|clippy|fmt|doc)( {{safe_chars}}+)*$"
action = { type = "Allow" }
.Ed
.Ss Git Operations
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[[bash_rules]]
name = "allow\-git\-read"
pattern = "^git (status|diff|log|show)"
action = { type = "Allow" }

[[bash_rules]]
name = "ask\-git\-write"
pattern = "^git (commit|push|pull|rebase)"
action = { type = "Ask" }

[[bash_rules]]
name = "deny\-git\-force"
pattern = "^git\e\es+push.*\-\-force"
action = { type = "Deny", value = "Force push is not allowed" }
.Ed
.Ss Comprehensive Security
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[pattern_fragments]
safe = "[^|&;$\`()<>{}]"
safe_arg = "( {{safe}}+)"

[[bash_rules]]
name = "deny\-rm\-rf\-root"
pattern = "^rm\e\es+\-rf\e\es+/"
action = { type = "Deny", value = "Cannot delete from root" }

[[bash_rules]]
name = "deny\-sudo"
pattern = "^sudo\e\eb"
action = { type = "Deny", value = "sudo not allowed" }

[[bash_rules]]
name = "allow\-read\-commands"
pattern = "^(ls|cat|head|tail|grep|wc|find){{safe_arg}}*$"
action = { type = "Allow" }

[[bash_rules]]
name = "allow\-cargo"
pattern = "^cargo (build|check|test|clippy|fmt){{safe_arg}}*$"
action = { type = "Allow" }
.Ed
.Sh TROUBLESHOOTING
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Em Rule not matching
Check logs at
.Pa ~/.local/state/moriarty/logs/
to see which rule matched:
.Pp
.Dl tail \-f ~/.local/state/moriarty/logs/moriarty\-*.log | grep \(lqBash rule matched\(rq
.It Em Pattern expansion errors
Check for undefined fragments, circular dependencies, or invalid
fragment names.
.It Em Unexpected modifications
Check
.Cm Modify
rules and their capture groups in the logs:
.Pp
.Dl tail \-f ~/.local/state/moriarty/logs/moriarty\-*.log | grep \(lqCommand modified\(rq
.It Em Rules not loading
Verify the config file exists at the expected path,
check TOML syntax, and look for parse errors in the logs.
.It Em Testing patterns
Use
.Cm moriarty test bash\-rules
to test a command against your rules,
or use an online regex tester with the Rust regex flavor.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml
Tool and bash rules configuration file.
.It Pa ~/.local/state/moriarty/logs/
Log files showing rule evaluation details.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr moriarty 1 ,
.Xr moriarty\-tool\-rules 5
